WEBVTT

00:00:00.010 --> 00:00:00.190
[The theme is handmade]

00:00:00.190 --> 00:00:01.750
Make Dubai chewy cookies.

00:00:01.750 --> 00:00:02.970
How about making desserts?

00:00:02.970 --> 00:00:03.070
Hello, express delivery for you.

00:00:03.070 --> 00:00:04.340
[Manito Gift-Giving Battle that lasted 2 days]

00:00:04.340 --> 00:00:05.780
Who are you? Who are you?

00:00:05.780 --> 00:00:06.980
Why are you running so fast?

00:00:06.980 --> 00:00:08.490
I told you I could do it!

00:00:08.490 --> 00:00:08.890
See! She came and left!

00:00:08.890 --> 00:00:10.260
[What's their new mission?]

00:00:10.260 --> 00:00:11.390
What's with him?

00:00:11.390 --> 00:00:13.790
[HQ: To become an official member
of Manito Club,]

00:00:13.940 --> 00:00:14.940
[HQ: you have to share the warmth]

00:00:15.060 --> 00:00:16.090
[HQ: you received from each other]

00:00:16.300 --> 00:00:18.460
[HQ: with the rest of the world
through a Secret Manito mission.]

00:00:18.460 --> 00:00:19.150
Are we a team?

00:00:19.150 --> 00:00:20.220
[The 6 gathered here are a team]

00:00:20.220 --> 00:00:20.420
The location?

00:00:20.420 --> 00:00:21.410
[Who's the recipient of the Secret Manito gift?]

00:00:21.410 --> 00:00:22.360
Where is it?

00:00:22.650 --> 00:00:23.880
[Secret Manito: Bucheon Fire Station]

00:00:23.880 --> 00:00:24.720
Bucheon Fire Station.

00:00:24.720 --> 00:00:24.820
[What do they need?]

00:00:24.820 --> 00:00:26.150
Let's do what they need.

00:00:26.150 --> 00:00:26.630
I've seen a lot of footage of them
being dispatched during mealtimes.

00:00:26.630 --> 00:00:29.870
[Firefighters who are frequently dispatched
even during mealtimes]

00:00:29.940 --> 00:00:31.420
Let's cook for them.

00:00:31.420 --> 00:00:32.950
We can make supper for them.

00:00:33.040 --> 00:00:34.930
[How about making something new?]

00:00:34.980 --> 00:00:35.080
It should be crispy. I'm stir-frying it.

00:00:35.080 --> 00:00:36.680
[Made by Younjung: upgraded Dubai chewy cookies]

00:00:36.890 --> 00:00:37.940
[Stir-frying kadayif excitedly]

00:00:37.940 --> 00:00:39.250
You're good at it!

00:00:39.250 --> 00:00:39.610
Since there are pistachios,

00:00:39.610 --> 00:00:40.820
[Contributing novel ideas]

00:00:40.820 --> 00:00:43.030
how about putting a few pistachios
before adding the cream?

00:00:43.030 --> 00:00:43.460
A Manito version.

00:00:43.460 --> 00:00:44.410
[Manito Club's Dubai chewy puffs has been created]

00:00:44.410 --> 00:00:45.590
Put rice cakes in it.

00:00:45.590 --> 00:00:47.050
-Rice cakes? -Yeah.

00:00:47.260 --> 00:00:48.690
[I was thinking about beef patties.]

00:00:48.690 --> 00:00:48.920
Add an abalone in it.

00:00:48.920 --> 00:00:51.300
[Add abalone for an energy boost]

00:00:51.300 --> 00:00:52.650
He did a good job.

00:00:52.650 --> 00:00:52.770
Do you usually cook?

00:00:52.770 --> 00:00:54.120
[An expert at pan-frying meat]

00:00:54.120 --> 00:00:56.160
I like cooking.

00:00:57.060 --> 00:00:57.410
It looks so yummy.

00:00:57.410 --> 00:00:58.320
[Made by Hae-in: Abalone Beef Patties]

00:00:58.320 --> 00:00:59.540
It looks so yummy.

00:00:59.750 --> 00:01:00.880
[How about knife-cut noodles?]

00:01:01.010 --> 00:01:01.020
How about Seafood Knife-Cut Noodles?

00:01:01.020 --> 00:01:02.330
[Main course of the nourishing meal]

00:01:02.580 --> 00:01:03.810
[Seafood Knife-Cut Noodles:
chock-full of nourishing ingredients]

00:01:03.810 --> 00:01:04.410
Is that octopus?

00:01:04.410 --> 00:01:05.450
Great, perfect.

00:01:05.450 --> 00:01:05.620
[Breathtaking sight that makes your mouth water]

00:01:05.620 --> 00:01:06.900
Wow, Yoon Namno.

00:01:06.900 --> 00:01:07.010
[Eggs are also nourishing (?)]

00:01:07.010 --> 00:01:08.760
Put one more here.

00:01:09.340 --> 00:01:09.500
[Chewing]

00:01:09.500 --> 00:01:10.750
Can you get me a pot of this size?

00:01:10.750 --> 00:01:12.520
[(Nods)]

00:01:12.610 --> 00:01:14.080
[(Caught ingesting nourishment)]

00:01:14.300 --> 00:01:15.080
[Made by Jinkyung: well-simmered broth]

00:01:15.080 --> 00:01:16.260
It's perfect.

00:01:16.260 --> 00:01:16.810
If we put effort into plating
to provide a VIP experience,

00:01:16.810 --> 00:01:19.130
[Meticulously prepared with warmth]

00:01:19.200 --> 00:01:19.320
I think it'll be more moving.

00:01:19.320 --> 00:01:20.730
[A warm nutritious meal for the firefighters]

00:01:20.730 --> 00:01:22.130
OK, shall we set off?

00:01:22.130 --> 00:01:22.150
[On their way to check out the fire station!]

00:01:22.150 --> 00:01:23.070
It's here. Bucheon Fire Station.

00:01:23.070 --> 00:01:23.830
We're here.

00:01:23.830 --> 00:01:23.960
Please come to the back door. I'll guide you in.

00:01:23.960 --> 00:01:26.950
[Can they sneak in smoothly?]

00:01:27.350 --> 00:01:27.450
Go, go, go.

00:01:27.450 --> 00:01:28.710
[On the way to meet their Secret Manito]

00:01:28.710 --> 00:01:30.530
I think this is the place.

00:01:31.200 --> 00:01:32.530
[Oh? Oh!]

00:01:32.850 --> 00:01:34.509
[Jung Hae-in: Hello.]

00:01:34.759 --> 00:01:35.970
[Wait, he didn't make a heart sign!]

00:01:35.970 --> 00:01:36.400
Make a heart sign.

00:01:36.400 --> 00:01:38.090
[Decided on a "heart" secret code
to identify their helper]

00:01:38.090 --> 00:01:40.250
Then we'll know it's you, OK?

00:01:40.250 --> 00:01:41.330
Hello.

00:01:41.590 --> 00:01:41.990
["Heart" secret code confirmed]

00:01:41.990 --> 00:01:42.920
A heart sign.

00:01:42.920 --> 00:01:43.690
He did it.

00:01:43.690 --> 00:01:44.200
Hello.

00:01:44.200 --> 00:01:45.580
[Successfully meet their helper]

00:01:45.580 --> 00:01:46.970
This way, please.

00:01:46.990 --> 00:01:47.400
Be quiet! Be quiet!

00:01:47.400 --> 00:01:51.410
[Following the helper to enter the station]

00:01:51.850 --> 00:01:54.640
[Employees on duty still at work inside]

00:01:57.780 --> 00:01:59.759
[Stealthily]

00:02:01.060 --> 00:02:02.490
We didn't disguise ourselves.

00:02:02.490 --> 00:02:03.960
[We are completely defenseless...]

00:02:04.140 --> 00:02:04.530
-Yeah. -We mustn't be caught.

00:02:04.530 --> 00:02:06.780
[Emergency disguise]

00:02:07.330 --> 00:02:10.300
[Moving to a safe place deep inside]

00:02:10.699 --> 00:02:12.040
-Hello. -Hello.

00:02:12.040 --> 00:02:13.510
-Hello. -Hello.

00:02:13.510 --> 00:02:15.350
[Staff lounge in the fire station's basement]

00:02:16.050 --> 00:02:16.180
[Officially meet their helpers
in the fire station]

00:02:16.180 --> 00:02:17.460
-Here. -Hello.

00:02:19.010 --> 00:02:21.180
[Hong Jinkyung: I didn't know
there was such a space in the fire station...]

00:02:21.180 --> 00:02:23.010
[Shh!]

00:02:23.270 --> 00:02:24.870
[Goodness...]

00:02:24.950 --> 00:02:25.340
Your hushing was louder.

00:02:25.340 --> 00:02:26.200
[Too immersed in the situation]

00:02:26.200 --> 00:02:28.030
He's suddenly so immersed.

00:02:28.030 --> 00:02:28.610
Your "shh" was louder.

00:02:28.610 --> 00:02:29.480
[Anyway, they've successfully sneaked in]

00:02:29.480 --> 00:02:30.930
Lift up your chairs.

00:02:30.930 --> 00:02:31.940
OK.

00:02:33.030 --> 00:02:33.079
[Team Leader Shim Hoseong,
Fire Prevention and Life Safety Team]

00:02:33.079 --> 00:02:34.270
Hello. Hello.

00:02:35.630 --> 00:02:36.610
OK. OK. OK.
[Assistant Manager Choi Juyong,
Fire Prevention and Life Safety Team]

00:02:36.610 --> 00:02:37.890
We're set. We're set.

00:02:37.980 --> 00:02:40.070
[Park Myungsoo: How many people
are there in your station?]

00:02:42.000 --> 00:02:44.579
[Around 70 daytime admin staff members.]

00:02:44.579 --> 00:02:47.540
There are about 30 members available for dispatch.

00:02:47.540 --> 00:02:49.390
There are 30 to 40 members on duty right now.

00:02:49.390 --> 00:02:50.550
[Around 30 nighttime staff members]

00:02:50.550 --> 00:02:51.220
They're all in this building?

00:02:51.220 --> 00:02:52.480
Yes, at work right now.

00:02:52.490 --> 00:02:55.270
[Hong Jinkyung: When it's busy,
how many times are you dispatched in a day?]

00:02:55.360 --> 00:02:58.040
There were 16 rescue cases...

00:02:58.060 --> 00:02:59.750
-Today? -Yes.

00:02:59.820 --> 00:03:01.320
There were 14 fire cases.

00:03:01.320 --> 00:03:02.480
Fires?

00:03:02.610 --> 00:03:04.450
[And about 65 emergency cases.]

00:03:04.450 --> 00:03:05.620
65 cases?

00:03:05.620 --> 00:03:06.580
We have 10 ambulances at our station.

00:03:06.580 --> 00:03:08.680
[Shocking volume of emergency dispatch]

00:03:08.680 --> 00:03:10.490
Bucheon is a small area,

00:03:10.490 --> 00:03:12.120
[Bucheon has a high population density]

00:03:12.120 --> 00:03:14.490
but it's densely populated.

00:03:14.490 --> 00:03:18.040
Within Gyeonggi Province, in 2025,

00:03:18.040 --> 00:03:21.040
we had the second highest
number of rescue dispatches

00:03:21.160 --> 00:03:24.380
and the highest number of emergency dispatches.

00:03:25.420 --> 00:03:30.190
Compared nationwide, we also have
one of the highest numbers of dispatches.

00:03:30.570 --> 00:03:33.560
[(Helper) Choi Juyong: Our staff's
work fatigue levels are pretty high.]

00:03:33.840 --> 00:03:35.510
[Yoon Namno: There was once...]

00:03:35.840 --> 00:03:39.329
I had a really bad cut while slicing ginseng.

00:03:39.370 --> 00:03:41.340
A customer in the restaurant

00:03:41.370 --> 00:03:44.600
happened to work at a fire station.

00:03:44.790 --> 00:03:47.120
[Yoon Namno: They didn't hesitate at all.]

00:03:47.520 --> 00:03:49.480
After emergency treatment,
they took me to the hospital right away,

00:03:49.480 --> 00:03:51.440
even though they were on leave that day.

00:03:51.440 --> 00:03:52.260
They stayed with me throughout the treatment.

00:03:52.260 --> 00:03:54.510
[A paramedic who stayed with him
until he was discharged]

00:03:55.050 --> 00:03:59.329
It was like my parents were with me.

00:03:59.329 --> 00:04:00.890
It was very reassuring.

00:04:00.900 --> 00:04:04.210
I'd forgotten about it,
but now that I'm here, I'm reminded of it.

00:04:04.210 --> 00:04:05.710
[Hong Jinkyung: We'll put our gratitude]

00:04:05.850 --> 00:04:09.360
[Hong Jinkyung: into today's food!]

00:04:10.530 --> 00:04:11.100
[What time do you have dinner?]

00:04:11.100 --> 00:04:12.840
We usually have dinner at 5 PM.

00:04:12.840 --> 00:04:14.250
You eat early.

00:04:14.440 --> 00:04:16.269
[Yoon Namno: What time
do you usually have supper?]

00:04:16.600 --> 00:04:17.970
[We don't eat if it's too late.]

00:04:18.240 --> 00:04:19.510
[Usually at about 8 to 9 PM.]

00:04:19.510 --> 00:04:20.700
8 to 9 PM.

00:04:20.700 --> 00:04:22.900
Then 9 PM is better.

00:04:24.200 --> 00:04:27.240
[By the way, we'll have to cook here...]

00:04:27.330 --> 00:04:27.560
We need to look at the kitchen.

00:04:27.560 --> 00:04:28.250
[Today's actual purpose
is to inspect the kitchen]

00:04:28.250 --> 00:04:31.470
Could we have a look at the kitchen?

00:04:31.470 --> 00:04:31.900
I'm afraid our staff will get suspicious.

00:04:31.900 --> 00:04:34.390
[A Secret Manito mission
where they can't take action blatantly]

00:04:34.390 --> 00:04:35.720
Right?

00:04:35.980 --> 00:04:38.310
[Park Myungsoo: Let's make up a new show title.]

00:04:38.310 --> 00:04:40.950
Pretend we're shooting another show?

00:04:41.270 --> 00:04:43.800
[Let's call it "Documentary Theater (?) Hero."]

00:04:43.800 --> 00:04:44.760
-Hero... -It's a good name.

00:04:44.760 --> 00:04:44.830
[Disguise as a documentary show]

00:04:44.830 --> 00:04:45.830
"Hero" is good.

00:04:45.830 --> 00:04:47.470
Sounds good, "Hero."

00:04:47.700 --> 00:04:50.960
[Kim Dohoon: Namno and I
will follow the 2 helpers]

00:04:51.290 --> 00:04:53.930
[Kim Dohoon: and pretend
to be the documentary MCs.]

00:04:53.930 --> 00:04:55.710
We'll make excuses.

00:04:55.710 --> 00:04:59.390
You two have to be serious,
so it's convincing as a documentary.

00:04:59.390 --> 00:05:01.960
-Have a serious attitude. -Yes.

00:05:01.960 --> 00:05:04.820
Let's get moving then.

00:05:04.820 --> 00:05:06.700
Ah, I'm bad at lying.

00:05:06.860 --> 00:05:09.690
Making commentary in secret
feels like a variety show though, haha.

00:05:09.690 --> 00:05:11.460
-You can do it! -You can do it!

00:05:11.540 --> 00:05:13.620
[Since it's a documentary, don't smile too much.
You have a smiley face.]

00:05:13.900 --> 00:05:15.530
-I have a smiley face? -Yes, don't smile.

00:05:15.530 --> 00:05:16.820
I've never heard that in my life.

00:05:16.820 --> 00:05:18.560
Don't smile. Put on a serious face.

00:05:18.560 --> 00:05:18.650
Don't smile too much.

00:05:18.650 --> 00:05:20.470
[(Actually quite happy to hear that)]

00:05:20.560 --> 00:05:21.090
[A fan meeting before their infiltration]

00:05:21.090 --> 00:05:23.550
We often talk about you over meals, Actress Go.

00:05:23.550 --> 00:05:25.090
-Really? -Yes.

00:05:25.190 --> 00:05:26.400
[Go Younjung: Thank you for watching my drama.]

00:05:26.400 --> 00:05:27.610
[Cha Muhee, Ddo Rami.]

00:05:27.870 --> 00:05:28.880
[Not "Ddo" like crazy, but Do Rami.]

00:05:28.880 --> 00:05:30.700
-Do Rami. -Do Rami.

00:05:30.780 --> 00:05:31.940
[I've watched up to Episode 11.]

00:05:31.970 --> 00:05:33.150
Really? Only 1 episode left.

00:05:33.150 --> 00:05:34.500
Only the finale left.

00:05:34.650 --> 00:05:35.800
[(Joking) It's a sad ending.]

00:05:35.800 --> 00:05:36.060
Really? I was hoping for a happy ending.

00:05:36.060 --> 00:05:38.610
[Shocked]

00:05:39.400 --> 00:05:41.070
[Go Younjung: I want to go up
(for the inspection),]

00:05:41.070 --> 00:05:42.740
[Go Younjung: but news about
me doing this show was released.]

00:05:42.750 --> 00:05:43.050
It'll be total chaos if you show up.

00:05:43.050 --> 00:05:45.750
[She can only wait inside so they're not exposed]

00:05:45.750 --> 00:05:45.909
[119 Bucheon Fire Station]
[A proper tour of the station]

00:05:45.909 --> 00:05:47.280
Let's visit the rescue team first.

00:05:47.280 --> 00:05:49.360
-Let's go. -Please follow me.

00:05:50.580 --> 00:05:52.270
It's not far from here.
[First, visit the rescue team
in the annex building]

00:05:52.270 --> 00:05:54.400
About 10 meters, about 5 meters.

00:05:54.400 --> 00:05:56.260
-It's right beside it. -Yes.

00:05:56.450 --> 00:05:58.290
[Monitoring the real-time situation
in the lounge]

00:05:58.290 --> 00:05:59.440
We can see them.

00:06:02.580 --> 00:06:05.060
[Rescue team]

00:06:05.490 --> 00:06:07.290
[The fire trucks are so cool!]

00:06:08.310 --> 00:06:10.920
[The dispatch alarm suddenly rings]

00:06:11.080 --> 00:06:12.740
[They're being dispatched now.]

00:06:18.710 --> 00:06:20.880
They got a report.

00:06:20.880 --> 00:06:21.390
[Dispatch alarm that's also heard in the lounge]

00:06:21.390 --> 00:06:24.280
Rescue dispatch! Rescue dispatch!

00:06:24.280 --> 00:06:26.310
There are really so many rescue reports.

00:06:26.310 --> 00:06:27.460
Please set off now.

00:06:27.950 --> 00:06:31.240
[The rescue team sets off swiftly]

00:06:37.780 --> 00:06:38.150
What do we do? Hide?

00:06:38.150 --> 00:06:38.930
[Surprised]

00:06:38.930 --> 00:06:39.659
OMG.

00:06:40.640 --> 00:06:41.210
[We're here to make a documentary.]

00:06:41.210 --> 00:06:42.130
Yeah, we're fine.

00:06:42.130 --> 00:06:43.610
-We don't have to hide. -No need to hide.

00:06:43.610 --> 00:06:44.850
[Yoon Namno: Because I'm a coward...]

00:06:44.850 --> 00:06:46.909
Am I about to see this with my own eyes?

00:06:47.920 --> 00:06:48.920
[It's canceled.]

00:06:48.920 --> 00:06:50.510
-Canceled? -Yes.

00:06:50.510 --> 00:06:50.740
Someone reported it and then canceled it.

00:06:50.740 --> 00:06:53.810
[Fortunately, the call was cancelled]

00:06:54.159 --> 00:06:54.350
[Relieved, they enter the rescue team's premises]

00:06:54.350 --> 00:06:56.290
-Hello. -Hello.

00:06:57.190 --> 00:07:00.240
[The staff return to the office and regroup]

00:07:00.730 --> 00:07:03.120
[Another dispatch
after barely catching their breaths]

00:07:03.120 --> 00:07:05.500
Rescue dispatch! Rescue dispatch!

00:07:05.500 --> 00:07:07.690
Respected by many...

00:07:07.690 --> 00:07:08.000
There are many reasons.

00:07:08.000 --> 00:07:08.730
[The alarm rings again]

00:07:08.730 --> 00:07:10.870
There's another dispatch.

00:07:12.230 --> 00:07:13.850
[(Helper) Shim Hoseong: Stay close to the wall.]

00:07:13.850 --> 00:07:14.780
[S-Should we leave first?]

00:07:14.780 --> 00:07:15.570
-Yes, go downstairs first. -Make way for them.

00:07:15.570 --> 00:07:18.170
[Wait outside, so they don't disrupt the dispatch]

00:07:18.530 --> 00:07:21.160
It's happened twice in 5 minutes.

00:07:21.370 --> 00:07:22.130
Time to set off!

00:07:22.130 --> 00:07:26.490
[The rescue team comes out in a hurry again]

00:07:26.810 --> 00:07:30.030
[Moves out immediately]

00:07:30.280 --> 00:07:31.620
[Yoon Namno: Those who came downstairs]

00:07:31.770 --> 00:07:32.720
[Yoon Namno: were those
who went upstairs just now, right?]

00:07:32.720 --> 00:07:33.720
Yes.

00:07:34.950 --> 00:07:36.360
[They really set off right away.]

00:07:36.480 --> 00:07:38.460
-It took less than 10 seconds, right? -Yes.

00:07:38.460 --> 00:07:40.210
Really fast.

00:07:40.210 --> 00:07:40.360
-Hello. -Hello.

00:07:40.360 --> 00:07:42.880
[Wearing earbuds to communicate with
the other cast members, as they enter the office]

00:07:42.880 --> 00:07:45.300
-Hello. -They're here for

00:07:45.300 --> 00:07:46.620
the documentary "Hero."

00:07:46.620 --> 00:07:52.060
[Trying to interview the remaining employees]
We're... like exploring... like what happens
over the course of 24 hours

00:07:52.070 --> 00:07:53.540
in the fire station.

00:07:53.540 --> 00:07:53.650
[A bit awkward, but quite convincing]

00:07:53.650 --> 00:07:55.230
That's what we're doing.

00:07:56.330 --> 00:07:59.280
[Kim Dohoon: We're going to record
the narration later. So we came in person.]

00:07:59.280 --> 00:08:00.930
-We have to see it with our own eyes. -Yes.

00:08:00.930 --> 00:08:04.190
Good job. They're doing good.

00:08:04.190 --> 00:08:04.320
They'll check out
the daily routine of firefighters

00:08:04.320 --> 00:08:06.370
[Kim Daejoong, Leader of Rescue Team 3]

00:08:06.910 --> 00:08:07.890
[Park Heesoo, Rescue Team 3]

00:08:07.890 --> 00:08:09.590
and ask some questions.

00:08:09.990 --> 00:08:11.910
[To apply to be rescue team members,]

00:08:12.290 --> 00:08:18.190
[you need at least 2 years
of experience in the special forces]

00:08:19.230 --> 00:08:21.140
[You're all really handsome.]

00:08:21.380 --> 00:08:21.520
No, no.

00:08:21.520 --> 00:08:23.620
[Shy]

00:08:24.220 --> 00:08:28.720
[Q. What do you hope
citizens can offer help with?]

00:08:28.950 --> 00:08:30.940
[Just like today, we came back after a mission.]

00:08:31.240 --> 00:08:33.470
[Kim Daejoong: We couldn't get through
because of an illegally parked car.]

00:08:33.470 --> 00:08:35.260
We called them, but they didn't answer.

00:08:35.260 --> 00:08:37.200
After calling many times, he finally picked up.

00:08:37.200 --> 00:08:39.390
[Kim Daejoong: In a very cold tone,
he said he'll drive it out now.]

00:08:39.500 --> 00:08:40.669
[But he didn't show up.]

00:08:41.159 --> 00:08:44.320
[Kim Daejoong: So we had to request
for legally parked cars to make way for us.]

00:08:44.880 --> 00:08:45.910
[That was really infuriating.]

00:08:45.910 --> 00:08:47.680
Of course. In such a situation.

00:08:47.680 --> 00:08:48.860
It made me mad.

00:08:49.190 --> 00:08:52.040
[Q. Do you have any taboos?]

00:08:52.380 --> 00:08:53.680
[Not really.]

00:08:53.680 --> 00:08:56.530
But there are things that we don't say.

00:08:56.760 --> 00:08:57.770
[Like, why it's so quiet today?]

00:08:57.870 --> 00:08:59.150
[Please don't say that.]

00:08:59.150 --> 00:08:59.700
Really? Sorry.

00:08:59.700 --> 00:09:00.670
[Oops...]

00:09:01.210 --> 00:09:01.380
[Forbidden words in the fire station]

00:09:01.380 --> 00:09:03.000
Oh, I see.

00:09:03.000 --> 00:09:04.660
We don't say things like that.

00:09:07.500 --> 00:09:10.150
Based on the severity of the emergency,

00:09:10.200 --> 00:09:12.090
is the alarm different?

00:09:12.100 --> 00:09:14.530
Like Code Blue in the hospital.

00:09:14.680 --> 00:09:16.300
[Kim Dohoon: There's something
I've been curious about.]

00:09:16.450 --> 00:09:17.600
[Kim Dohoon: Can I ask another question?]

00:09:18.070 --> 00:09:23.550
[Kim Dohoon: Is there a different alarm
according to the severity of the situation?]

00:09:23.550 --> 00:09:25.150
-Like hospitals... -They're all different.

00:09:25.150 --> 00:09:28.060
One for fires, one for rescues,
and one for emergencies.

00:09:28.060 --> 00:09:30.710
[The dispatch alarms that ring
dozens of times a day]

00:09:31.340 --> 00:09:34.870
[The difference between
the fire, rescue, and emergency alarm]

00:09:36.380 --> 00:09:40.990
[The 1st dispatch alarm: begins solemnly]

00:09:41.280 --> 00:09:43.210
[Fire dispatch! Fire dispatch!]

00:09:43.970 --> 00:09:48.140
[Fires that can result in major casualties
even with a slight delay]

00:09:48.280 --> 00:09:49.050
Something happened on Basement One.

00:09:49.050 --> 00:09:52.300
[In charge of putting out fires,
rescue, and risk elimination]

00:09:52.300 --> 00:09:54.500
The smell is from Basement One.

00:09:54.760 --> 00:09:59.050
[The fire team
who wipes out the panic in the city]

00:09:59.280 --> 00:10:01.110
As assistance on the fire scene...

00:10:01.110 --> 00:10:02.920
[Gets up] [Gets up]

00:10:03.400 --> 00:10:06.510
[The 2nd dispatch alarm: most frequently heard]

00:10:07.230 --> 00:10:09.450
[Rescue dispatch! Rescue Dispatch!]

00:10:10.330 --> 00:10:14.980
[In charge of emergency patients
and hospital transportation]

00:10:16.140 --> 00:10:19.640
[The rescue team rushes
to stay within the golden hour]

00:10:20.690 --> 00:10:24.620
[The 3rd dispatch alarm: the last one]

00:10:24.620 --> 00:10:26.350
[Rescue dispatch!]

00:10:27.270 --> 00:10:30.890
[In charge of lifesaving and risk elimination]

00:10:31.420 --> 00:10:34.610
[The rescue team who saves lives
on the front lines]

00:10:35.110 --> 00:10:37.860
[Jung Hae-in: These are things
the viewers probably didn't know.]

00:10:37.860 --> 00:10:39.620
[I didn't know either!]

00:10:39.870 --> 00:10:43.400
[(Helper) Shim Hoseong: He's a chef,
so he's the most curious about what we eat.]

00:10:43.400 --> 00:10:45.060
I said we all eat differently.

00:10:45.270 --> 00:10:46.860
[We usually eat whatever we have, haha.]

00:10:46.890 --> 00:10:48.060
[Something that's fast.]

00:10:48.240 --> 00:10:50.160
[Things we can eat later
even if we leave it to go on missions.]

00:10:50.460 --> 00:10:51.780
[A menu suited to irregular dispatches]

00:10:51.780 --> 00:10:53.100
That's what we usually eat.

00:10:53.100 --> 00:10:53.260
-Enjoy. -Enjoy.

00:10:53.260 --> 00:10:56.630
[Late at night, in the rescue team's office]

00:10:57.510 --> 00:10:59.070
[Today's supper is fried chicken and pizza]

00:10:59.070 --> 00:11:00.950
I should have ordered more.

00:11:00.950 --> 00:11:02.600
It's OK. I'll just eat less.

00:11:02.600 --> 00:11:03.510
There's instant noodles too.

00:11:03.510 --> 00:11:07.680
[Kim Daejoong: Even if we can't finish the pizza
and fried chicken, we can eat it when we return.]

00:11:07.830 --> 00:11:10.820
[Kim Daejoong: Other than instant noodles,
we don't have food with soups.]

00:11:10.980 --> 00:11:11.580
It's cheap, so we won't feel wasteful
even if we don't get to finish it.

00:11:11.580 --> 00:11:15.740
[Restricted supper choices
because of frequent dispatches]

00:11:18.930 --> 00:11:23.610
[Free time is only temporary;
the bell rings again]

00:11:23.610 --> 00:11:25.800
Rescue dispatch! Rescue dispatch!

00:11:27.310 --> 00:11:29.310
[Yoon Namno: If you're dispatched
in the middle of eating,]

00:11:29.460 --> 00:11:31.200
[Yoon Namno: I feel like
your appetite will be ruined.]

00:11:31.270 --> 00:11:31.430
I think so too.

00:11:31.430 --> 00:11:33.700
[That's right.]

00:11:34.680 --> 00:11:35.280
Oh, I see.

00:11:35.280 --> 00:11:36.600
[Jung Hae-in: But their interview]

00:11:36.860 --> 00:11:37.870
[is done well like a documentary.]

00:11:38.100 --> 00:11:38.700
[I agree.]

00:11:38.700 --> 00:11:39.870
Like a documentary.

00:11:39.870 --> 00:11:40.390
You have great bodies.

00:11:40.390 --> 00:11:41.050
[The first round of interviews
went better than expected]

00:11:41.050 --> 00:11:41.790
I'm jealous.

00:11:41.790 --> 00:11:44.550
-Thank you. -Here.

00:11:47.070 --> 00:11:50.910
Is this exclusive to this team, or...

00:11:51.260 --> 00:11:54.680
[The slogan is pasted everywhere]

00:11:54.690 --> 00:11:56.110
[First In Last Out]
[Gyeonggi Province Fire Station]

00:11:56.130 --> 00:12:00.060
[First In Last Out]
[The first to go in; the last to come out]

00:12:00.800 --> 00:12:08.480
[For the safety of the citizens,
with a strong sense of duty,]

00:12:09.310 --> 00:12:14.710
[they go in first and come out last]

00:12:14.830 --> 00:12:17.160
First in; last out.

00:12:17.420 --> 00:12:21.140
[The first to go in; the last to come out.]

00:12:21.140 --> 00:12:23.110
So cool. So solemn.

00:12:23.110 --> 00:12:25.510
-The last to come out. -The last to come out.

00:12:25.760 --> 00:12:28.430
[(Helper) Shim Hoseong:
But it's not easy to stick to it.]

00:12:28.570 --> 00:12:30.720
[(Helper) Shim Hoseong:
To go in first and come out last.]

00:12:30.840 --> 00:12:33.290
[(Helper) Shim Hoseong: So we have to
strengthen our resolve all the time.]

00:12:33.530 --> 00:12:36.940
[(Helper) Shim Hoseong: It is
what's in the "Firefighters' Prayer."]

00:12:36.970 --> 00:12:37.230
[Firefighters' Prayer:
God! When I'm summoned, no matter how big
the fire, please give me strength to save a life.
Let me embrace a child
and save a frightened elder before it's too late.]

00:12:37.230 --> 00:12:38.990
We think about it over and over again,

00:12:38.990 --> 00:12:40.030
to try our best to do as it says.

00:12:40.030 --> 00:12:42.380
[Give me the ability to ensure safety
at all times, to hear the weakest screams,
and put out fires quickly and efficiently.]

00:12:42.380 --> 00:12:43.770
It's hard for us too.

00:12:43.770 --> 00:12:43.980
[Let me fulfill my duty to do my best
to protect every life and property.]

00:12:43.980 --> 00:12:46.250
We're scared too.

00:12:46.250 --> 00:12:47.150
But if we don't do it, no one will.

00:12:47.150 --> 00:12:51.710
[If fate be it that my life ends,
may God's grace bless my spouse and family.]

00:12:51.710 --> 00:12:52.910
Of course I'm scared.

00:12:54.120 --> 00:12:54.130
I'm lying if I say I'm not scared.

00:12:54.130 --> 00:12:58.030
[Lee Takjoon, Fire Extinguishing Team 3]

00:12:59.320 --> 00:13:04.330
[I'm scared.]

00:13:04.760 --> 00:13:06.350
[Lee Takjoon: Arriving at the scene,]

00:13:08.330 --> 00:13:11.440
[Lee Takjoon: the moment I see the fire,
I get scared.]

00:13:11.690 --> 00:13:14.530
[Lee Takjoon: The team leaders
usually go in first.]

00:13:15.490 --> 00:13:17.630
[I can only trust them and follow them.]

00:13:17.970 --> 00:13:20.080
[Lee Yoseob: I can't see anything inside.]

00:13:20.220 --> 00:13:22.300
[Lee Yoseob: Not even things in front of me.]

00:13:22.440 --> 00:13:25.500
[Lee Yoseob: I can only rely on the person
in front of me and move forward.]

00:13:25.650 --> 00:13:26.060
Yes, they're my lifeline.

00:13:26.060 --> 00:13:28.280
[Colleagues are lifelines]

00:13:28.500 --> 00:13:30.790
[Kang Yeonik: If the team leader
hesitates at the beginning,]

00:13:30.930 --> 00:13:32.800
[Kang Yeonik: the others will also hesitate.]

00:13:33.630 --> 00:13:36.910
[Kang Yeonik: So the team leaders
must lead by example.]

00:13:37.180 --> 00:13:41.950
[Jo Seondeok: I'm the center director,
in charge of command and other tasks.]

00:13:42.500 --> 00:13:46.870
[Jo Seondeok: If I make a wrong judgment
or give a wrong order,]

00:13:47.040 --> 00:13:48.660
[Jo Seondeok: more citizens may get hurt.]

00:13:48.800 --> 00:13:50.910
[Jo Seondeok: Or the fire might spread.]

00:13:51.420 --> 00:13:55.460
[My judgment may jeopardize
the lives of my colleagues.]

00:13:55.460 --> 00:13:57.600
This is what's really tough.

00:13:57.600 --> 00:13:58.030
[Always bearing a heavy sense of responsibility]

00:13:58.030 --> 00:14:02.740
It's a constant heavy burden inside.

00:14:02.740 --> 00:14:04.170
I keep thinking about this.

00:14:04.170 --> 00:14:06.560
I go in first and I come out last.

00:14:06.560 --> 00:14:09.890
I'm sure the team leaders feel it the most.

00:14:09.890 --> 00:14:12.100
This is the leader, the rescue team leader.

00:14:12.100 --> 00:14:14.190
-Just now we... -Rescue Team Leader.

00:14:14.190 --> 00:14:14.200
[Salute]

00:14:14.200 --> 00:14:16.200
How do we salute? Do we say "victory"?

00:14:16.200 --> 00:14:18.360
[(Helper) Shim Hoseong:
We usually say "safety."]

00:14:18.680 --> 00:14:20.970
[1, 2, 3. Safety slogan (?)]

00:14:21.420 --> 00:14:21.600
-Safety! -Safety!

00:14:21.600 --> 00:14:23.680
[(Rescue team leader) Kim Geonwon: Safety!]

00:14:23.680 --> 00:14:25.620
-Thank you. -Have a safe drive home!

00:14:25.620 --> 00:14:26.250
[Thank you for your hard work!]

00:14:26.250 --> 00:14:27.880
Have a safe drive home!

00:14:30.340 --> 00:14:32.170
-Isn't this nice? -So this is the fitness room.

00:14:32.170 --> 00:14:32.810
-Hello. -Hello.

00:14:32.810 --> 00:14:33.960
[Fitness Room]

00:14:33.960 --> 00:14:36.770
We have better facilities than other departments.

00:14:36.770 --> 00:14:37.160
I relieve stress through exercise.

00:14:37.160 --> 00:14:39.240
[Members who spare time to stay in shape]

00:14:39.240 --> 00:14:41.030
You don't rest but exercise.

00:14:41.030 --> 00:14:42.690
Many of them do that.

00:14:43.020 --> 00:14:45.430
[It's the smell of tough man.]

00:14:45.790 --> 00:14:47.210
[Hello.]

00:14:47.380 --> 00:14:48.630
-Hello. -Hello.

00:14:48.630 --> 00:14:49.520
[Lee Yoseob, Fire Extinguishing Team 3]

00:14:49.520 --> 00:14:51.430
We're here for the documentary "Hero."

00:14:51.430 --> 00:14:53.230
He has a great body.

00:14:53.720 --> 00:14:57.670
[Namno! Touch the biceps
of the person in front of you.]

00:14:57.670 --> 00:14:58.910
Touch his biceps.

00:14:58.910 --> 00:15:01.060
[Quivering lips]

00:15:01.120 --> 00:15:03.780
[About to burst out laughing]

00:15:04.260 --> 00:15:04.300
-Since he loves working out. -He's going.

00:15:04.300 --> 00:15:06.480
[Slightly hesitant]

00:15:06.480 --> 00:15:07.550
He's doing it.

00:15:07.550 --> 00:15:08.970
[Woah!]

00:15:09.270 --> 00:15:10.560
[Wow, amazing.]

00:15:10.560 --> 00:15:12.010
No, no. Thank you.

00:15:12.660 --> 00:15:14.220
[Ask him to make a few cool poses.]

00:15:14.220 --> 00:15:15.600
Make some cool poses.

00:15:15.900 --> 00:15:16.610
[What if we're exposed?]

00:15:16.610 --> 00:15:18.310
"Make a few cool poses."

00:15:18.590 --> 00:15:20.180
[Then hang on his biceps.]

00:15:20.200 --> 00:15:20.230
[Pft]

00:15:20.230 --> 00:15:21.660
Go on.

00:15:22.680 --> 00:15:24.040
Go on!

00:15:24.370 --> 00:15:24.560
[Hahaha] [Hahaha] [Hahaha]

00:15:24.560 --> 00:15:25.930
-He... Please make a few cool poses.

00:15:25.930 --> 00:15:27.360
He's holding back his laughter.

00:15:27.360 --> 00:15:28.660
[Hahaha] [Hahaha]

00:15:28.820 --> 00:15:28.950
[Hahaha] [Hahaha]

00:15:28.950 --> 00:15:31.260
-He can't keep his laughter in!
-And hang on his biceps.

00:15:31.260 --> 00:15:32.110
[Struggling]

00:15:32.110 --> 00:15:35.390
Can you do a pose to show us your biceps?

00:15:35.390 --> 00:15:38.010
-Could he... -Could I hang on them?

00:15:39.650 --> 00:15:42.350
[If you wish]

00:15:42.350 --> 00:15:43.440
OMG.

00:15:43.440 --> 00:15:44.520
[Wow!]

00:15:45.250 --> 00:15:47.390
[Trembling]

00:15:49.860 --> 00:15:51.310
[His feet are off the ground!]

00:15:51.650 --> 00:15:54.030
[Falls immediately]

00:15:54.270 --> 00:15:55.300
[Even muscular men
can't withstand the weight of Namno]

00:15:55.300 --> 00:15:56.730
He failed.

00:15:58.680 --> 00:15:59.880
OMG.

00:15:59.880 --> 00:16:01.500
Anyway, after working out...

00:16:01.500 --> 00:16:02.810
[Kim Dohoon: Those into fitness]

00:16:02.950 --> 00:16:04.370
[Kim Dohoon: always say nutrition
is part of working out.]

00:16:04.370 --> 00:16:04.900
Yes, that's right.

00:16:04.900 --> 00:16:07.050
[Kim Dohoon: What do you eat after working out?]

00:16:07.390 --> 00:16:09.540
[Lee Yoseob: I don't follow a diet plan.]

00:16:09.540 --> 00:16:11.940
I just eat a lot.

00:16:11.940 --> 00:16:13.460
-Eat a lot? -Yeah.

00:16:13.700 --> 00:16:16.740
[Yoon Namno: To people like you,
who have burly bodies...]

00:16:16.840 --> 00:16:20.980
What protein food would you recommend?

00:16:20.980 --> 00:16:22.780
-I like beef. -Beef...

00:16:24.920 --> 00:16:27.120
-So you like beef patties too, right? -Yes, I do.
[Subtly hinting]

00:16:27.120 --> 00:16:27.420
I see.

00:16:27.420 --> 00:16:29.120
[Score]

00:16:29.120 --> 00:16:29.360
All the best!

00:16:29.360 --> 00:16:30.010
[Weight loss]

00:16:30.010 --> 00:16:31.500
All the best. Thank you for your hard work.

00:16:31.500 --> 00:16:32.810
Thank you.

00:16:33.550 --> 00:16:34.010
[Central 119 Security Center]

00:16:34.010 --> 00:16:35.440
Hello.

00:16:36.260 --> 00:16:37.220
Hello.

00:16:37.650 --> 00:16:40.050
[119] [Bucheon Fire Station]
[Central 119 Security Center]

00:16:40.240 --> 00:16:41.800
[Fire, Rescue, Emergency]

00:16:43.020 --> 00:16:45.090
[Fire]

00:16:45.640 --> 00:16:46.860
[Emergency]

00:16:47.180 --> 00:16:48.690
[Life Safety]

00:16:49.200 --> 00:16:52.700
[Busiest department in Bucheon Fire Station]

00:16:53.230 --> 00:16:55.980
[(Helper) Choi Juyong:
The center director is here.]

00:16:56.020 --> 00:16:58.830
-Hello. -Hello.

00:16:58.830 --> 00:16:59.490
She heard you were filming a documentary,
so she didn't go home.

00:16:59.490 --> 00:17:02.660
[Jo Seondeok, director
of Central 119 Security Center]

00:17:02.880 --> 00:17:04.380
[Say "I love you, Center Director!"]

00:17:04.680 --> 00:17:05.849
[Say "I love you, Center Director!"]

00:17:05.849 --> 00:17:06.890
I love you?

00:17:06.890 --> 00:17:07.210
[Put on the spot]

00:17:07.210 --> 00:17:08.680
Say it! "Center..."

00:17:08.680 --> 00:17:09.050
Dohoon, say "I love you, Center Director!"

00:17:09.050 --> 00:17:10.900
[An unreasonable romantic]

00:17:11.089 --> 00:17:12.220
[Hesitant]

00:17:12.390 --> 00:17:13.319
I love you, Center Director.

00:17:13.319 --> 00:17:16.290
OMG. What should I do?

00:17:16.319 --> 00:17:19.960
[Next, sing. "I love you..."]

00:17:20.290 --> 00:17:22.960
I love you.
[Love is all about momentum!]

00:17:23.109 --> 00:17:23.430
I love you. I really love you.

00:17:23.430 --> 00:17:26.270
[Devoting a dance of love to her]

00:17:26.630 --> 00:17:29.620
[A confession that's slightly burdensome head-on]

00:17:30.240 --> 00:17:31.870
Namno.

00:17:31.870 --> 00:17:32.000
I really love you.

00:17:32.000 --> 00:17:34.880
[Persistent]

00:17:37.830 --> 00:17:40.150
[Even my husband's never done this for me.]

00:17:40.570 --> 00:17:40.630
Well, the question we were on was

00:17:40.630 --> 00:17:42.740
[Calms down and gets down to business]

00:17:42.740 --> 00:17:44.370
actually a simple question.

00:17:44.490 --> 00:17:49.040
[Kim Dohoon: What's the most
rewarding aspect of your job?]

00:17:49.830 --> 00:17:52.620
[Park Yoonju: It has to be
on the scene of rescue.]

00:17:53.270 --> 00:17:57.540
[When they say I'm doing a good job.]

00:17:57.660 --> 00:17:59.920
Oh, when they say you're doing a good job.

00:17:59.980 --> 00:18:03.220
[Lee Yoseob: When we emerge
from the fire scene after putting it out...]

00:18:03.700 --> 00:18:05.030
[When they thank us.]

00:18:05.030 --> 00:18:06.760
When they say "thank you" to us.

00:18:06.900 --> 00:18:09.180
[It's most rewarding when they thank us.]

00:18:09.780 --> 00:18:12.700
[Bae Giseok: Even if they are
just passing by, they say hello]

00:18:12.700 --> 00:18:15.140
[Bae Giseok: and cheer for us.
I'm really grateful for these.]

00:18:16.020 --> 00:18:18.580
[Kang Yeonik: All firefighters
probably feel the joy from it.]

00:18:18.580 --> 00:18:21.780
[Kang Yeonik: Whenever we save lives
and put out fires...]

00:18:22.750 --> 00:18:24.750
When we feel like we've saved lives.

00:18:25.500 --> 00:18:28.190
["So I guess I chose the right job."]

00:18:28.190 --> 00:18:30.190
That's how I feel.

00:18:31.380 --> 00:18:34.060
[Yoon Namno: Will you choose to
be a firefighter in your next life?]

00:18:34.460 --> 00:18:37.140
[Yes, I will.]

00:18:40.700 --> 00:18:45.060
[If you'd choose to be a firefighter
in your next life, could you raise your hand?]

00:18:45.700 --> 00:18:49.620
[A swarm of hands raised]

00:18:50.380 --> 00:18:53.380
[Lee Yoseob: My name was
given by my grandfather.]

00:18:54.100 --> 00:18:59.100
[Lee Yoseob: "Yo" meaning "save,"
and "seob" meaning "flame."]

00:18:59.740 --> 00:19:02.660
It's a bit like destiny.

00:19:03.500 --> 00:19:06.380
[Jo Seondeok: Is it just because it's our job
that we can enter a fire scene?]

00:19:07.740 --> 00:19:10.900
[Jo Seondeok: People often say
it's a sense of duty...]

00:19:11.620 --> 00:19:14.420
[But you can't do it with just a sense of duty.]

00:19:15.780 --> 00:19:17.220
[Maybe it's destiny.]

00:19:18.500 --> 00:19:18.850
[Maybe it's destiny.]

00:19:18.850 --> 00:19:20.150
So I just keep on at it.

00:19:20.900 --> 00:19:22.580
[Korea Fire Service]

00:19:23.260 --> 00:19:23.650
[Cafeteria]

00:19:23.650 --> 00:19:24.410
So this is it.

00:19:24.510 --> 00:19:27.110
This is where we get our food and have our meals.

00:19:27.220 --> 00:19:27.300
[Entering the stage of
the Secret Manito mission]

00:19:27.300 --> 00:19:28.760
They're at the cafeteria.

00:19:29.760 --> 00:19:30.480
Looks nice.

00:19:30.900 --> 00:19:31.420
It's here.

00:19:31.420 --> 00:19:32.700
[We've to take a good look here!]

00:19:32.900 --> 00:19:34.580
[This is the main deal.]

00:19:35.000 --> 00:19:35.260
Have a look at the stoves and stuff.

00:19:35.260 --> 00:19:37.230
[The kitchen,
the main arena of the Secret Manito mission]

00:19:37.230 --> 00:19:39.000
-It's good. -You can use everything.

00:19:39.000 --> 00:19:40.010
A dishwasher.

00:19:41.700 --> 00:19:42.700
There's a grill here.

00:19:42.700 --> 00:19:47.380
[The head chef checks the kitchen carefully]

00:19:47.490 --> 00:19:49.370
You can keep it warm here.

00:19:50.460 --> 00:19:51.780
[Get your food here]
[Hmm...]

00:19:51.780 --> 00:19:54.020
[Hmm...]

00:19:54.420 --> 00:19:57.340
[Yoon Namno: Can the others
come and take a look at the cafeteria too?]

00:19:57.460 --> 00:19:59.540
[(Helper) Shim Hoseong:
They have to be discreet.]

00:20:00.180 --> 00:20:03.650
[The other members join them discreetly]

00:20:03.650 --> 00:20:05.040
-Not bad. -It's close.

00:20:05.100 --> 00:20:07.180
[Park Myungsoo: How is it?
Will things work out?]

00:20:07.180 --> 00:20:09.090
-Yes, here... -Is it OK?

00:20:09.220 --> 00:20:10.820
[Hong Jinkyung: But the problem is
if we cook here,]

00:20:10.820 --> 00:20:12.300
[Hong Jinkyung: they can
see everything from outside.]

00:20:12.300 --> 00:20:13.900
-Yes. -We have to cover it up.

00:20:13.940 --> 00:20:15.020
[Yoon Namno: This is all open.]

00:20:15.020 --> 00:20:16.940
[We'll cover it up till here
like ramen restaurants.]

00:20:17.160 --> 00:20:17.620
Like ticket counters.

00:20:17.620 --> 00:20:18.690
[Suggests to cover it up except for
a small opening, like a ticket counter]

00:20:18.690 --> 00:20:19.830
Then only our hands are visible.

00:20:19.830 --> 00:20:20.780
-Yeah. -Sounds good.

00:20:20.780 --> 00:20:21.570
[Like a vending machine!]

00:20:21.570 --> 00:20:22.460
Like a vending machine.

00:20:22.460 --> 00:20:23.440
Well...

00:20:23.580 --> 00:20:26.640
[Hong Jinkyung: But there are always
people who are curious and peep inside.]

00:20:26.640 --> 00:20:27.640
It's me. I do that.

00:20:27.650 --> 00:20:29.180
Wondering what's going on.

00:20:29.540 --> 00:20:31.300
[I'm the type to open the door to see.]

00:20:31.620 --> 00:20:33.660
[Dohoon's the type to chase after you.]

00:20:34.020 --> 00:20:36.020
[Don't tell me they'll stick their hands in
like a vending machine?]

00:20:37.620 --> 00:20:38.780
[It must be fun.]

00:20:38.860 --> 00:20:38.980
[Manito Club members are really excited]

00:20:38.980 --> 00:20:40.000
It'll be fun.

00:20:40.700 --> 00:20:41.690
[Shall we do a hand-stack and cheer?]

00:20:41.690 --> 00:20:42.610
Come on! Come on!

00:20:42.610 --> 00:20:43.340
Come on!

00:20:43.860 --> 00:20:44.900
[For success!]

00:20:44.900 --> 00:20:45.980
1, 2, 3!

00:20:46.180 --> 00:20:48.780
[Let's go!]

00:20:49.050 --> 00:20:49.850
Let's set off.

00:20:52.780 --> 00:20:56.700
[Secret Manito: D-DAY]

00:20:56.980 --> 00:20:57.610
[Cooking Studio]

00:20:57.610 --> 00:20:59.330
-Hello. -Hello, hello.

00:20:59.410 --> 00:21:01.670
-I'm here. I bought abalone. -OK.

00:21:01.890 --> 00:21:02.900
Put the dessert here.

00:21:02.900 --> 00:21:02.990
[Before the fire station infiltration,
the members gather for the cooking prep]

00:21:02.990 --> 00:21:04.330
-Put it here? -Yes.

00:21:05.250 --> 00:21:06.250
-Put the beef patties there. -Hello.

00:21:06.250 --> 00:21:06.760
Hello.

00:21:06.820 --> 00:21:08.220
-Put the beef patties there. -Beef patties?

00:21:08.220 --> 00:21:08.260
Let's gather in the middle first.

00:21:08.260 --> 00:21:10.030
[Strategizing before starting]

00:21:10.030 --> 00:21:11.980
-Gather here first. -Just a moment.

00:21:11.980 --> 00:21:13.780
[Yoon Namno: Today is a special situation.]

00:21:13.780 --> 00:21:15.540
[Yoon Namno: It's not for customers,
but firefighters.]

00:21:15.770 --> 00:21:17.290
They could be dispatched

00:21:17.290 --> 00:21:19.070
-in the middle of their meal. -Yes.

00:21:19.070 --> 00:21:20.100
So we'll provide after-service.

00:21:20.100 --> 00:21:22.130
[Provide fresh meals again when they return]

00:21:22.130 --> 00:21:23.500
Make the exact same meal.

00:21:23.500 --> 00:21:27.100
The target was 30 servings,
but we'll double it into 60 servings.

00:21:28.860 --> 00:21:30.420
[Yoon Namno: So time is tight.]

00:21:30.420 --> 00:21:30.920
[Original version of the supper:
Seafood Knife-Cut Noodles, Abalone Beef Patties,
and Dubai chewy puffs]

00:21:30.920 --> 00:21:33.650
There are some additional things to take note of.

00:21:34.500 --> 00:21:35.250
[Add color to the Seafood Knife-Cut Noodles]

00:21:35.250 --> 00:21:36.350
To add color,

00:21:36.410 --> 00:21:37.940
we'll add red peppers and green onion,

00:21:37.940 --> 00:21:38.270
[Red peppers] [Green onions] [Whole octopus leg]

00:21:38.270 --> 00:21:39.800
which we didn't add before.

00:21:41.580 --> 00:21:44.300
[Added turmeric rice, to eat with soup]

00:21:44.430 --> 00:21:45.060
And for the beef patties,

00:21:45.060 --> 00:21:46.250
[And the upgraded Abalone Beef Patties]

00:21:46.250 --> 00:21:48.340
we were only making it with abalone.

00:21:48.570 --> 00:21:48.580
Now we'll add one more thing: truffle on top.

00:21:48.580 --> 00:21:51.060
[Adds truffle]

00:21:51.060 --> 00:21:52.220
[Portions increased too!]

00:21:52.220 --> 00:21:53.020
Truffle too.

00:21:53.900 --> 00:21:56.180
[Yoon Namno: Truffle and beef are a good match.
Truffle and abalone too.]

00:21:56.570 --> 00:21:57.580
Their flavors go well together.

00:21:57.580 --> 00:21:57.900
[Nods]

00:21:57.900 --> 00:21:58.480
OK, OK.

00:21:58.540 --> 00:21:59.620
That's what I've prepared.

00:21:59.620 --> 00:22:01.370
[Manito version of Dubai chewy cookies:
Dubai chewy puffs]

00:22:01.370 --> 00:22:02.220
We'll use rice cakes instead of marshmallows.

00:22:02.220 --> 00:22:07.620
[Replace marshmallows
with the chewier rice cakes]

00:22:08.820 --> 00:22:12.600
[Upgraded menu after days of deliberation]

00:22:12.600 --> 00:22:16.380
[Turmeric rice] [Dubai chewy puff]
[Seafood Knife-Cut Noodles] [Abalone Beef Patty]

00:22:16.820 --> 00:22:17.340
OK, I've organized everything down here.

00:22:17.340 --> 00:22:20.660
[Namno has even meticulously
split up the workload]

00:22:20.800 --> 00:22:21.940
I'll assign the work now.

00:22:21.940 --> 00:22:25.670
[In charge of Truffle Abalone Beef Patties:
Hae-in & Dohoon]

00:22:25.670 --> 00:22:26.980
You're familiar with it, since we've done it once.

00:22:26.980 --> 00:22:27.380
[Hae-in is in charge of
the beef patties and pan-frying]

00:22:27.380 --> 00:22:29.700
Just do as we did, and make them nicely.

00:22:29.780 --> 00:22:29.790
[Dohoon is in charge of prepping the abalone
and assisting with the beef patties]

00:22:29.790 --> 00:22:31.260
-Dohoon will do the abalone. -OK.

00:22:31.260 --> 00:22:33.140
-Try to get it done quickly. -Yes, sir.

00:22:33.140 --> 00:22:35.380
[Yoon Namno: And for the hardest task.]

00:22:35.870 --> 00:22:35.980
Hae-in, Dohoon, and Myungsoo

00:22:35.980 --> 00:22:38.200
[Hae-in & Dohoon & Myungsoo:
make the noodles for Seafood Knife-Cut Noodles]

00:22:38.200 --> 00:22:40.460
will make the knife-cut noodles by hand.

00:22:41.320 --> 00:22:42.320
Make the dough.

00:22:42.680 --> 00:22:43.890
The dough and everything.

00:22:43.890 --> 00:22:45.270
When Jinkyung arrives...

00:22:45.270 --> 00:22:47.770
Jinkyung's good at Korean food,
so she'll make the rice.

00:22:47.770 --> 00:22:47.860
She'll cook the rice

00:22:47.860 --> 00:22:49.030
[Jinkyung:
Seafood Knife-Cut Noodles + turmeric rice]

00:22:49.030 --> 00:22:52.340
and be in charge of
seasoning the ginseng chicken soup.

00:22:52.780 --> 00:22:53.420
She's good at seasoning.

00:22:53.420 --> 00:22:54.580
[The broth...]

00:22:54.660 --> 00:22:56.220
[Yoon Namno: She won't need my help with it.]

00:22:56.220 --> 00:22:58.540
[Yoon Namno: She'll be fully in charge of it.]

00:22:58.830 --> 00:22:59.660
-Younjung will take charge of the dessert. -OK.

00:22:59.660 --> 00:23:02.000
[Younjung: Dubai chewy puffs]

00:23:02.000 --> 00:23:03.460
The dessert is the last dish.

00:23:03.460 --> 00:23:06.100
[Yoon Namno: At a BBQ restaurant, we get mad
when the final fried rice tastes bad, right?]

00:23:06.100 --> 00:23:06.780
-It's the worst. -Yes.

00:23:06.780 --> 00:23:09.110
[Why are you only
putting pressure on me?]

00:23:10.180 --> 00:23:13.380
[Do you know how important the abalone is?
I'm so stressed out.]

00:23:13.620 --> 00:23:16.860
[If it tastes fishy, it's Dohoon's fault.]

00:23:17.060 --> 00:23:18.820
[Ah...]

00:23:19.040 --> 00:23:19.100
I should instruct like this then.

00:23:19.100 --> 00:23:22.380
[Professional responsibility is a must today!]

00:23:23.020 --> 00:23:24.540
[Yoon Namno: I've taught you once,]

00:23:24.540 --> 00:23:27.260
[Yoon Namno: so this time,
you'll be responsible for your tasks,]

00:23:27.260 --> 00:23:29.180
[Yoon Namno:
and I'll be in charge of inspection]

00:23:29.180 --> 00:23:30.500
[Yoon Namno: and supporting you.]

00:23:31.110 --> 00:23:31.340
-Chef. -Chef.

00:23:31.340 --> 00:23:32.470
[Yoon Namno: in charge of difficult tasks,
demanding work, teaching, and providing support]

00:23:32.470 --> 00:23:33.260
Chef.

00:23:33.340 --> 00:23:33.950
Chef, here.

00:23:33.950 --> 00:23:35.260
-Chef! -Chef!

00:23:35.360 --> 00:23:36.420
-Chef. -Coming!

00:23:36.420 --> 00:23:36.790
[Yoon Namno]

00:23:36.790 --> 00:23:37.340
Here, Chef.

00:23:37.340 --> 00:23:40.820
[Head chef, Namno]

00:23:40.820 --> 00:23:41.290
[Schedule
11:00–17:00: Cooking Prep
17:00–19:00: Head to the Fire Station
19:00–21:00 Late-Night Restaurant Prep
21:00-24:00: Open for Business]

00:23:41.290 --> 00:23:42.460
-Shall we start? -OK.

00:23:42.460 --> 00:23:45.400
The back kitchen is for actual cooking.

00:23:45.460 --> 00:23:46.870
This is the prep area.

00:23:47.160 --> 00:23:47.380
It's currently 11:30 AM.

00:23:47.380 --> 00:23:49.220
[5 hours and 30 minutes left]

00:23:49.420 --> 00:23:51.740
[Kim Dohoon: I brought a watch from home.]

00:23:52.220 --> 00:23:52.400
[Personal watch]

00:23:52.400 --> 00:23:53.760
To confirm the time.

00:23:53.840 --> 00:23:54.970
Since time is tight.

00:23:55.300 --> 00:23:57.350
I'll be the human alarm clock today.

00:23:58.020 --> 00:23:59.700
[Reliable]

00:24:01.780 --> 00:24:04.740
[Simmering fresh chickens to make the broth
for the Seafood Knife-Cut Noodles]

00:24:05.100 --> 00:24:08.420
[Amazing amount of chicken for 60 servings]

00:24:08.420 --> 00:24:11.620
[(Make the broth first)]

00:24:11.940 --> 00:24:15.460
Behind! Behind!
[The broth that takes a long time is simmered
in the back kitchen with strong burners]

00:24:15.580 --> 00:24:19.580
[Support according to the procedure]

00:24:19.580 --> 00:24:25.860
[Seafood Knife-Cut Noodles:
Prep and boil the raw chickens
Make the broth
Prep the octopus and vegetable garnish
De-bone the chickens
Make the noodles]

00:24:26.860 --> 00:24:28.460
[Kim Dohoon: Should I fill it with water?]

00:24:28.940 --> 00:24:28.980
Let me teach you how to clean the abalone well.

00:24:28.980 --> 00:24:31.940
[Fresh]

00:24:32.940 --> 00:24:33.900
[Clumsy]

00:24:33.900 --> 00:24:35.380
[Is this your first time seeing live abalone?]

00:24:35.500 --> 00:24:37.380
[It's my first time seeing it and touching it.]

00:24:37.980 --> 00:24:39.190
[(Scared) Can I do something else?]

00:24:39.190 --> 00:24:40.100
No.

00:24:40.340 --> 00:24:40.780
[Instead, he explains how to clean it patiently]

00:24:40.780 --> 00:24:41.950
Touch here first.

00:24:42.940 --> 00:24:44.580
[It's slippery, right?] [Yes.]

00:24:45.660 --> 00:24:48.660
[Yoon Namno: (Brush it)
in cold water for 5-6 times...]

00:24:49.600 --> 00:24:50.410
Here, here.

00:24:50.660 --> 00:24:50.820
[Squeaky clean]

00:24:50.820 --> 00:24:52.180
-Until it's squeaky clean. -Squeaky clean.

00:24:52.180 --> 00:24:53.340
[Yoon Namno: It's enough]

00:24:53.340 --> 00:24:55.700
[Yoon Namno: when it feels clean
like after you do the dishes.]

00:24:56.060 --> 00:24:57.160
-Like this. -OK.

00:24:57.190 --> 00:24:59.670
-Then stack them up one by one in here. -OK.

00:24:59.750 --> 00:25:00.220
Then...

00:25:00.220 --> 00:25:00.440
[Truffle Abalone Beef Patties:
Clean and boil the abalone
Make the beef patty sauce
Shape the beef patties
Knead the meat]

00:25:00.440 --> 00:25:01.570
So this is an important task.

00:25:01.570 --> 00:25:02.630
-This is very important. -Only one brush?

00:25:02.630 --> 00:25:04.010
-Sorry? -There's only one brush.

00:25:04.010 --> 00:25:05.540
We need to make the dessert.

00:25:07.450 --> 00:25:09.230
This... The kadayif...

00:25:09.760 --> 00:25:09.980
Cut them into the size like last time,
and fill this bowl.

00:25:09.980 --> 00:25:13.720
[Kadayif: key ingredient of the Dubai chewy puffs,
Manito Club's spin on Dubai chewy cookies]

00:25:13.720 --> 00:25:14.280
Spread them out?

00:25:14.280 --> 00:25:14.380
-Then put them in the oven. -OK.

00:25:14.380 --> 00:25:15.770
[Younjung's first task:
cut the kadayif and bake them]

00:25:15.770 --> 00:25:16.530
Bake them.

00:25:16.860 --> 00:25:22.340
[Dubai chewy puffs:
Cut and bake the kadayif
Cut the rice cakes and puffs
Portion out the jam
Make the cream]

00:25:22.620 --> 00:25:26.060
[Prepping 60 servings of kadayif]

00:25:26.300 --> 00:25:29.500
[Cut it into 1-cm pieces that are easy to eat]

00:25:30.820 --> 00:25:32.420
[Hehe]

00:25:35.020 --> 00:25:37.740
[(Next plate)]

00:25:38.220 --> 00:25:40.220
[On to her 2nd plate]

00:25:41.180 --> 00:25:42.940
[Spreads them out evenly]

00:25:43.300 --> 00:25:46.220
[Quickly]

00:25:46.220 --> 00:25:49.780
[Dubai chewy puffs:
Cut and bake the kadayif]

00:25:49.940 --> 00:25:52.170
[Yoon Namno: Bake them for 10 minutes first.]

00:25:52.170 --> 00:25:54.380
-Then continue at 3-minute intervals. -OK.

00:25:54.380 --> 00:25:56.180
[Yoon Namno: You need to
stir them from time to time.]

00:25:57.220 --> 00:25:59.580
[Takes it out from the oven]

00:25:59.940 --> 00:26:02.700
[Stirs them evenly]

00:26:03.420 --> 00:26:08.780
[Back and forth,
it consumes both stamina and patience]

00:26:08.940 --> 00:26:09.360
[Dubai chewy puffs PREP %]
[One plate of kadayif is done]

00:26:09.360 --> 00:26:10.960
-Is this enough? -Very good.

00:26:12.500 --> 00:26:18.420
[The white kadayif has
turned golden brown after baking]

00:26:19.340 --> 00:26:21.090
[Go Younjung: Bake it a little longer?]

00:26:21.090 --> 00:26:22.260
-No, it's just right. -Just right?

00:26:22.260 --> 00:26:23.660
-It's crispy and good. -OK.

00:26:23.660 --> 00:26:23.980
-Bake the other plate just like that. -OK.

00:26:23.980 --> 00:26:25.260
[(Finished checking the kadayif)]

00:26:26.500 --> 00:26:30.060
[Using this gap in time to check the broth
of the Seafood Knife-Cut Noodles]

00:26:30.580 --> 00:26:32.490
[(Next dish)]

00:26:32.490 --> 00:26:33.210
Wait.

00:26:33.260 --> 00:26:35.100
[Goes to Hae-in
who's in charge of the beef patties]

00:26:35.340 --> 00:26:37.340
[Yoon Namno: Hae-in, this is striploin.]

00:26:37.340 --> 00:26:37.520
[Korean beef foreshank] [Korean beef striploin]

00:26:37.520 --> 00:26:38.520
Which part is that?

00:26:38.520 --> 00:26:39.980
-Foreshank. -Foreshank.

00:26:40.860 --> 00:26:43.340
[Yoon Namno: You usually
don't use striploin for beef patties.]

00:26:43.820 --> 00:26:45.980
[Is it too high-quality?]
[Totally.]

00:26:46.700 --> 00:26:49.660
[Put abalone and truffle]

00:26:50.100 --> 00:26:53.740
[on the Korean beef striploin and foreshank]

00:26:54.140 --> 00:26:58.140
[Handmade Truffle Abalone Beef Patties]

00:26:58.140 --> 00:27:00.660
[Truffle Abalone Beef Patties:
Make the beef patty sauce]

00:27:00.780 --> 00:27:03.010
[Yoon Namno: The sauce ratio
was 5 to 3 to 2 last time, right?]

00:27:03.010 --> 00:27:03.580
5 to 3 to 2.

00:27:03.580 --> 00:27:03.810
[Today: 5 (soy sauce) to 2.5 (sugar) to 2 (mirin)]
(T/N: mirin = Japanese cooking wine)

00:27:03.810 --> 00:27:06.890
But today, it's 5 to 2.5 to 2.

00:27:07.060 --> 00:27:08.760
-5 to 2.5 to 2. -5 is soy sauce.

00:27:09.860 --> 00:27:09.940
[The ratio of soy sauce to sugar to mirin
has become more complicated]

00:27:09.940 --> 00:27:11.530
-2.5 is sugar. -Sugar.

00:27:11.580 --> 00:27:12.130
Sugar.

00:27:12.190 --> 00:27:13.320
-2 is mirin. -Mirin.

00:27:13.430 --> 00:27:15.280
-But that... -Mirin is...

00:27:15.330 --> 00:27:17.250
-Wait. -The sugar is 2.5.

00:27:17.300 --> 00:27:17.470
[Calculate the ratio with 3 liters of soy sauce]

00:27:17.470 --> 00:27:19.070
-This is 2 liters. -2 liters.

00:27:19.390 --> 00:27:20.900
Pour 1 more liter.

00:27:21.220 --> 00:27:22.580
[Soy sauce "5" = 3 liters]

00:27:23.060 --> 00:27:24.820
[Mirin "2" = 1.2 liters]

00:27:25.420 --> 00:27:26.340
[Sugar "2.5" = 1.5 kg]

00:27:27.170 --> 00:27:27.970
5 is soy sauce.

00:27:28.730 --> 00:27:29.510
2 is mirin.

00:27:30.830 --> 00:27:32.630
And 2.5 is sugar.

00:27:34.940 --> 00:27:37.060
[Mix it evenly]

00:27:37.180 --> 00:27:39.580
[Add scallion, garlic, onion, and minced ginger]

00:27:40.620 --> 00:27:44.460
[Blend all the ingredients in the blender]

00:27:47.620 --> 00:27:49.540
[Truffle Abalone Beef Patties:
Make the beef patty sauce (ticked)]

00:27:49.540 --> 00:27:50.680
The sauce is ready.

00:27:52.300 --> 00:27:56.260
[Truffle Abalone Beef Patties PREP %]
[Dubai chewy puffs PREP %]

00:28:03.860 --> 00:28:07.060
[Looking around]

00:28:08.060 --> 00:28:10.060
[Chef!]

00:28:10.540 --> 00:28:11.180
Sorry, but is this clean enough?

